      "type": "aliange-lp-text-block",
      "settings": {
        "label": "The Problem",
        "headline": "The Beauty Industry's Biggest Flaw: The 'Routine'",
        "body": "<p>For decades, the beauty industry has sold us the concept of a skincare 'routine.' It usually involves buying a cleanser from one brand, a trending serum from another, and a moisturiser recommended by an influencer. You layer them on, hoping for the best.</p><p>But here is the clinical reality: when you mix and match products without a deep understanding of their molecular weights, pH levels, and cellular delivery mechanisms, you are likely cancelling out active ingredients—or worse, causing chronic barrier inflammation. This unstructured approach is why so many people hit a plateau, where their expensive anti-ageing products simply stop working.</p><p>At Aliangé, we do not believe in routines. We believe in <strong>Protocols</strong>.</p>",
        "bg": "muted",
        "width": "narrow",
